VulnLens is built and fully working. Here's what was created:

## VulnLens — Complete

**Structure:**
```
demo/
├── backend/
│   ├── main.py        # FastAPI app + all API routes
│   ├── rules.py       # Deterministic rule engine (10 OWASP patterns)
│   ├── database.py    # SQLite + 847-scan seed data
│   └── requirements.txt
├── frontend/
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── pages/Scanner.jsx      # Split-screen editor + results
│   │   ├── pages/Leaderboard.jsx  # Bar chart trends dashboard
│   │   ├── pages/Report.jsx       # Shareable read-only report page
│   │   └── components/            # CodeEditor, FindingCard, ScanHistory
│   └── dist/                      # Built and ready to serve
├── start.sh
└── README.md
```

**To run:**
```bash
./start.sh
# or manually:
pip install -r backend/requirements.txt
cd frontend && npm install && npm run build && cd ..
python backend/main.py
```
Open http://localhost:8000

**Verified working:**
- Deterministic scan detects SQL injection, hardcoded secrets, MD5, XSS, eval(), etc.
- API endpoints: `/api/scan`, `/api/report/:id`, `/api/history`, `/api/leaderboard`
- React SPA with CodeMirror editor, red line highlighting, Recharts bar chart
- Shareable reports at `/report/:id`, scan history sidebar, copy-as-Markdown export
- Seeded with 847 historical scans for the leaderboard
- AI review pass (Claude) enabled when `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY` is set; gracefully degrades without it
